Wonderful image!  Is this the departure for London?

The 'Asturias' sailed for London at 11am (11:40 by the Customs House clock!) on Saturday 21/3/1908. Passenger list etc - <a href="http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14947996" rel="nofollow">trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14947996</a> . - &quot;Included in the cargo are:  26,000 bxs butter, 450 bls wool, 150bls leather,  and over 20,000 cases of apples from Hobart.&quot;

The apples fetched from 6/3 (six shillings and threepence) per case in London in May - <a href="http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14944118" rel="nofollow">trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14944118</a>
